cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the impact of popularity-based rankings on online platforms, which is a topic related to social media and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses analytical and simulation methods to study the phenomenon, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the few-get-richer effect on the spread of misinformation, which could relate to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
